    answer: 'Increased sensitivity to peer opinion is a hallmark of the 8-to-10 age range. As children develop "social comparison" skills, they begin to measure their own abilities and appearance against their peers. This shift is a necessary part of developing a self-concept, though it can lead to temporary dips in confidence or increased self-consciousness.',
  },
